reviewText:
Of these five, I have three on other sets. They are all good movies, just be careful not to duplicate. Also, all five movies are on one disc, the picture quality is fine, but still 5 movies on one disc is cramping them. Then again, you don't have to change the disc to see the next one.

Ralph J. Fitcher
Pretty good set for the price, Mega Piranha, and Chupacabra vs. The Alamo (with Erik Estrada) were the best of the lot.
